content:
While I agree with your scum reads HD, I find it a little reckless to dump a L-2 vote on TCS with so much time remaining based on what you've read up to page 3. The least you can do is finish catching up before putting down this vote imo. <br>
<br>
@TCS - I agree my case is not strong. It's d1, and rarely will you see a strong case this early. I feel you're the best option right now, but there's still time for that to change. Your response to my pressure isn't bad.

@HD - I see one as more reactive and that was followed by strategic moves. I see the other as more of a genuine push. Do you see them differently than that?<br>
<br>
@Rev - I might consider L-2 to be vulnerable and if a scummy guy came in at that point and walked away I might buy into the shift. But he walked up to a L-4 wagon and didn't hop on it right away...color me less impressed. I want to know why that impresses you so much.<br>
<br>
Could you clarify your scumreads for yourself and then offer them to me in a clarified form?

@TCS - Rev hasn't been around long enough in order to appear patient or not.<br>
<br>
I certainly read it as reluctance to end the day - I'm just not sold on any alignment tells being particularly evident in the action other than, again, suspecting you to be town, but that's not a new thing for me so...meh.

@Rev - You were giving us self-meta of what you think you'd do as scum?<br>
<br>
@Purple Smear<br>
1. Spoken like someone scared to use their vote as a weapon or unwilling to defend their actions...though that seems self-evident.<br>
2. Whut? So you agree it look slike actively hunting? Otherwise known as 'something town should do'?<br>
3. Because scum have always historically been unable to tell who looks town without town's help.

@kashoodles, I appreciate the cramming and participation. 1,000 times better than YOLO. Not sure what to make of your pessimism regarding your odds of survival.<br>
<br>
My thing regarding Nacho was, and continues to be, that (along with Thor) he is going to be one of the most difficult players to read D1. The few points brought against him don't strike me as being outside his usual playstyle regardless of alignment. Maybe someone more familiar with his play can shed light?

@Rev - yes, a no lynch is better. Town aren't supposed to vote people they think are town - that's how the game is played.<br>
<br>
@HD - then, considering you're the flip you're advocating, you are dumb or scum.

@Thor: Keep puzzling over it if you need to. I'm just encouraging you to puzzle over MM as well, since she is likewise sheeping with no logic. As for who's working on HD &amp; TCS, "some of us" mostly just means "you", doesn't it? What are people working on right now anyway? Judging from the vote count and discussion on the last 2 pages, it seems people are currently working on YOU. While I can see why they would feel that your position makes no sense, I tend to agree with HD that you're just an easy target today.<br>
<br>
So please understand that I'm not speaking to those people who are in deep mental anguish trying to decide what they think of HD &amp; TCS, but the people who are on your wagon when they should be on MM's.

@Nacho: I'm not opposed to it, per se. I keep saying it's not going to happen not because I don't want it to happen, but becaue I truly believe that it won't. I don't see myself voting for him today because MM is a much better lynch in my opinion.<br>
<br>
MM, why on earth are you playing like green scum if you're not???

@Bacde - this about sums up why the wagon on me is so bad.<br>
<br>
@MM - other than, y'know, how we make no sense as partners at all, sure.

@Jun - seriously - a three man scumteam in a 9 player game? Tell me more.<br>
<br>
I need to go get inebriated before I have to read any more of this.

@Jun<br>
@TCS<br>
<br>
Seriously - what were you thinking was going on when I called Nacho scummy for not being aware of my case? Why wouln't you...y'know, say something like 'But Thor, you haven't presented a case so...lulz!" or, y'know, anything? You just watched that happene and shrugged it off as Thor being that horribly bad of a player or something? I mean, what about when Drummer admitted the case existed? Or MM? What about when she discussed it? I think Bacde did too - you figured they had all fallen under my spell or something?

@Thor do you think that you are confirmed town y/n?<br>
<br>
also, why don't you think Drummer is confirmed town?

@Thor do you think Jun is town?<br>
<br>
@HD quiet you, town is talking

@Bacde - vote me then.<br>
<br>
@HD - Why do I need to make a case on you? It's not like you're really making a case on anyone right now, so I'm not sure why I'm suddenly supposed to. But my basic case is 'PoE and lack of reason to call you town compared to a number of other players' Toss in a bit of 'under the radar' play for kicks and some 'gut' for flavor. That's about it.<br>
<br>
Edit- egads, vote splurge.<br>
<br>
@Bacde - I think Jun is town in the same way I think HD is town.

@Jun if you aren't going to try to convince Thor that TCS is scum and that I am town then go ahead and hammer me<br>
<br>
Thor isn't going to listen to my arguments and I don't want to play another Newbie 1340 where I fucking try try try my hardest and end up losing anyway due to someone being unwilling to consider other possibilities (which Thor doesn't seem to be doing)
